understand it and we KNEW what the commercial was supposed to be about.

The only time I saw Marketing for the C128 was the billboard in Vegas, and
teh thosands of flyers, proclaiming that the C128 was expandable to 512mb
(My boss had canned the MMU that supported this so wwe had to do it with DMA
after the fact) and I once read an article where they intervviewed Tom Dow
(they called him Tony Dow in the artcile) who shared that he was teh C128
project manager.  Only problem was I had never heard of him.  I promptly
went over and introduced myself figuriong that if he was running my project
I should at least take his measure.

Marketing?  Not reallyw hen I was there... better International, no school,
little consumer.

