play state-of-the-art games of 1994-1996. That's why I took the
PS1 vs CD32 into this discussion aswell, since the PS1 was offering
much much more than even an expanded A1200/CD32 did.

But there also was 386 PCs around, and everything was moving towards 3D
games the previous years already. Remember these games:

Comanche (1992)
Ultima Underworld (1992)
Wolfenstein 3D (1992)
Doom (1993)
Magic Carpet (1994)
Descent (1995)
Duke Nukem 3D (1996)
Tomb Raider (1996)

Some of these games even pre-date the release of the A1200 by years. And
those are only &quot;textured games&quot; examples. There was other 3D games using
flat shading which easily showed much greater performance on PC before,
but the textures really showed the difference to everyone.

Sorry, when the AGA Amigas came out, they already felt dated. And I say
this as a long years Amiga fan.
